---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Sources"
  description="A short list of public data and editorial reference sources used by College FAQ."
>
  <article class="max-w-editorial mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-aus-ink font-bold mb-8">Sources</h1>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>College FAQ articles are written from public institutional data, school-facing guidance, government resources, and clearly attributed editorial references.</p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl">Institutional Sources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>U.S. Department of Education</strong> — official federal education data and policy guidance</li>
        <li><strong>NCES</strong> — education statistics, enrollment data, and institutional reporting</li>
        <li><strong>College Scorecard</strong> — costs, outcomes, and school-level comparison data</li>
        <li><strong>Common Data Set</strong> — institution-published admissions and enrollment details</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl">Editorial References</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>NACAC</strong> — admissions counseling research and practice reports</li>
        <li><strong>College Board</strong> — testing, affordability, and application-cycle resources</li>
        <li><strong>University admissions offices</strong> — official program pages, deadlines, and application instructions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
